title: Dubuque Senior falls to Pleasant Valley 31-16
text:
Dubuque Senior falls to Pleasant Valley 31-16 - KWWL - Eastern Iowa Breaking News, Weather, Closings Member Center: Dubuque Senior falls to Pleasant Valley 31-16 Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> 
Homecoming week for Dubuque Senior, but this night belonged to Pleasant Valley. 
Dubuque Senior quarterback Lee Bonifas' first throw of the game is picked off. 
The Pleasant Valley offense wasted no time at all, striking on the very next play. Quarterback Terry Saul found wide receiver Alex Rodruck for the 24-yard score. 
The Rams respond with an impressive drive of their own, but Pleasant Valley holds and forces Rams kicker Ben Kubitz to hit a 22-yard field goal. 
Later, Pleasant Valley finishes a nice drive of their own, when Saul takes it in for the 1-yard keeper to put the Spartans up 14-6. 
Senior was able to move the ball all night, but just couldn't finish drives. They're held to another field goal, this time a 42-yarder. 
Saul finishes up yet another lengthy drive with a short keeper to put Pleasant Valley up 21-6 at the halftime. 
Senior put up a fight in the second half, finally breaking through with a touchdown. But the rushing attack of Pleasant Valley was too much, and they beat Senior 31-16.
